The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 14 June is 279,538 (32,218.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 09 June, there were 1,088 new confirmed cases (125.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 02 June, there were 705 new cases and so the new cases have risen by 54% (383 extra cases).
